Dolly the Kid-O is learning to count using her fingers - being a Left Hander she uses her LEFT hand to count the numbers - her mother being a Tech Savvy gives this as a test to her Bro Rahul , who loves numbers, he cracks it in 3 minutes. Think like him.
Thumb 	Index	Middle	Ring	Little
   5     4	  3	 2        1
Note : Counting begins from Little Finger to Thumb, Index to Little, Ring to Thumb and So on
Input : Integer [ 1 to 10^7]
Output : Name of the finger
Examples:
Input : 25
Output : Little

           SOLUTION:


n = int(input())

fingers = [
    "little",
    "Ring",
    "Middle",
    "Index",
    "Thumb",
    "Index",
    "Middle",
    "Ring"
]

print(fingers[(n - 1) % 8])

